        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "1. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A \\in \\mathbb { R } ^ { n \\times n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a non-singular matrix. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "u"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "v \\in \\mathbb { R } ^ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be column vectors. Define the rank 1 perturbation "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\stackrel { \\triangledown } { \\boldsymbol { A } } = \\boldsymbol { A } + u \\boldsymbol { v } ^ { T }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                106,
                219,
                856,
                256
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Derive a necessary and sufficient condition for "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\widehat { A }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "to be invertible. "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Let "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "x"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ", "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "z"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "and "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "b"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "be column vectors in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\mathbb { R } ^ { n }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". Suppose one can solve "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "A z = b"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "with "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "{ \\mathcal { O } } ( n )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "floating-point operations (flops). Under the conditions derived in(a), design an algorithm to solve "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "{ \\widehat { A } } x = b"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "with "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "{ \\mathcal { O } } ( n )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "flops, and provide justification for your answer. "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                138,
                268,
                854,
                368
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "2. Consider the integral "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                106,
                386,
                315,
                402
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\int_ {0} ^ {\\infty} f (x) d x",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/847317aa08cdf00c6376973ab64ae4e13a013d54628348129c0d251a2842c5dc.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                442,
                401,
                545,
                440
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is continuous, "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f ^ { \\prime } ( 0 ) \\neq 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f ( x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "decays like "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x ^ { - 1 - \\alpha }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\alpha > 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "in the limit "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x \\to \\infty"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                445,
                854,
                481
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(a) Suppose you apply the equispaced composite trapezoid rule with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "subintervals to approximate "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                138,
                498,
                854,
                532
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\int_ {0} ^ {L} f (x) d x.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/6344f20d25926b7e17e92614c17bc1d9315ad2ae51348b0cffa2339725aa2b23.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                464,
                532,
                566,
                571
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "What is the asymptotic error formula for the error in the limit "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n  \\infty"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "L"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "fixed? "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                169,
                577,
                854,
                612
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(b) Suppose you consider the quadrature from (a) to be an approximation to the full integral from 0 to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\infty"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". How should "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "L"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "increase with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "to optimize the asymptotic rate of total error decay? What is the rate of error decrease with this choice of L? 5 "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                138,
                619,
                854,
                690
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(c) Make the following change of variable "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x = { \\frac { L ( 1 + y ) } { 1 - y } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "L(1 + y) , "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "y = { \\frac { x - L } { x + L } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "x − L in the original integral to obtain "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                138,
                693,
                854,
                744
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\int_ {- 1} ^ {1} F _ {L} (y) d y.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/e3a9d0863a9abb6b944e7dec9e120a7ccadd45f389a1c974a53e83fef52b353e.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                457,
                744,
                570,
                784
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Suppose you apply the equispaced composite trapezoid rule; what is the asymptotic error formula for fixed "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "L"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "? "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                169,
                789,
                854,
                825
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(d) Depending on "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\alpha"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", which method - domain truncation or change-of-variable - is preferable? "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                138,
                830,
                854,
                868
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": []
            },
            "bbox": [
                464,
                890,
                473,
                902
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "3. Consider the Chebyshev polynomial of the first kind "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                106,
                138,
                576,
                155
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "T _ {n} (x) = \\cos (n \\theta), \\quad x = \\cos (\\theta), \\quad x \\in [ - 1, 1 ].",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/532a32cc436c5afaffd7ddd8eb6d2928c6523878688b13b5a2f74ca9fde53c29.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                305,
                171,
                679,
                191
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The Chebyshev polynomials of the second kind are defined as "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                130,
                210,
                653,
                228
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "U _ {n} (x) = \\frac {1}{n + 1} T ^ {\\prime} (x), \\quad n \\geq 0.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/142c277cf4d4fed559a71b1ab948d5bfd2c5ec5aa4d7ee3b5901950864fb233c.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                367,
                242,
                617,
                276
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Derive a recursive formula for computing "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "U _ { n } ( x )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "for all "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "n \\geq 0"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Show that the Chebyshev polynomials of the second kind are orthogonal with respect to the inner product "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                138,
                290,
                854,
                351
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\langle f, g \\rangle = \\int_ {- 1} ^ {1} f (x) g (x) \\sqrt {1 - x ^ {2}} d x",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/e6bac13c9dc7b4572759d339ff8b801d575b3d29fad9226afaafb88a662fbf42.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                377,
                367,
                651,
                407
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(c) Derive the 2-point Gaussian Quadrature rule for the integral "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                140,
                417,
                689,
                436
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\int_ {- 1} ^ {1} f (x) \\sqrt {1 - x ^ {2}} d x = \\sum_ {j = 1} ^ {2} w _ {j} f (x _ {j})",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/9fb7312e9f72dba399b2d2b3e05a05be869646d1a8776f057d2ae23ea1c4cae1.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                369,
                450,
                658,
                500
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "4. Consider the boundary value problem "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                106,
                516,
                455,
                532
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "- \\frac {d}{d x} \\left(a (x) \\frac {d u}{d x}\\right) = f (x), \\quad u (0) = u (1) = 0",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/ddbaa011f96efb3a7b5fbf22c8dcd2516895a9a4a3d05d9715b120ba7ef1db55.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                313,
                546,
                674,
                585
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "a ( x ) > \\delta \\geq 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a bounded differentiable function in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "[ 0 , 1 ]"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". We assume that, although "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "a ( x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is available, an expression for its derivative, "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\frac { d a } { d x }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is not available. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                598,
                854,
                651
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(a) Using finite differences and an equally spaced grid in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\lfloor 0 , 1 \\rfloor"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x _ { l } = h l , l = 0 , \\ldots , n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "h = 1 / n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", we discretize the ODE to obtain a linear system of equations, yielding an "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "O ( h ^ { 2 } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "approximation of the ODE. After the application of the boundary conditions, the resulting coefficient matrix of the linear system is an "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( n - 1 ) \\times ( n - 1 )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "tridiagonal matrix. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                138,
                662,
                854,
                753
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Provide a derivation and write down the resulting linear system (by giving the expressions of the elements). "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                169,
                758,
                854,
                794
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(b) Utilizing all the information provided, find a disc in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbb { C }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", the smaller the better, that is guaranteed to contain all the eigenvalues of the linear system constructed in part (a). "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                138,
                800,
                854,
                856
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "2 "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                462,
                888,
                475,
                902
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "5. (a) Verify that the PDE "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                106,
                138,
                352,
                155
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "u _ {t} = u _ {x x x}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/7189b173f27782c9f9eb46bd72adc28b2555074e4623a0b84421cea8a82a6777.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                475,
                161,
                555,
                174
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is well posed as an initial value problem. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                171,
                180,
                517,
                198
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(b) Consider solving it numerically using the scheme "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                203,
                589,
                220
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\frac {u (t + k , x) - u (t - k , x)}{2 k} = \\frac {- \\frac {1}{2} u (x - 2 h , t) + u (x - h , t) - u (x + h , t) + \\frac {1}{2} u (x + 2 h , t)}{h}.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/bf5f6950721125984377abbf3c4ba48bfccf42a700d8fd88707e5aa93f83ee65.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                176,
                229,
                888,
                267
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Determine this scheme’s stability condition. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                171,
                272,
                544,
                289
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "6. Consider the diffusion equation "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                104,
                301,
                398,
                319
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\frac {\\partial v}{\\partial t} = \\mu \\frac {\\partial^ {2} v}{\\partial x ^ {2}}, \\quad v (x, 0) = \\phi (x), \\quad \\int_ {a} ^ {b} v (x, t) d x = 0",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/e46ecc3e7efc2ac12e9484a961a42b051e841e527edee0fe1dfb54a283e1b3d2.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                289,
                327,
                700,
                367
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x \\in [ a , b ]"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and periodic boundary conditions. The solution is to be approximated using the central difference operator "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "L"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
